rComments: A lot of chances for extra credit; lab participation, discussion, and a news story is an easy 15% of your grade. Very approachable professor and is helpful that she just finished her PhD so she understands the struggle. She takes class time before exams to give a review of content. I didn't read the textbook once and I received an A+.
Exams are not reflective of class content, however she is willing to help you get through class with a good grade

Very clear and straightforward teaching, exams directly reflect lecture material. Not many assignments or labs, gives plenty of opportunity for easy extra credit. Easy to reach and responds to emails quickly. If you go to class, you'll pass this course no problem. I would definitely take a class with her again.
